t of people pray for power, house, financial breakthrough, wealth etc. But only few ask God for wisdom. There are so many great power pack man and women of God who lack wisdom.\n\n- Patience Johnson, Why Does an Orderly God Allow Disorder\n|\nAnd for the support of this declaration, with a firm reliance on the protection of divine providence, we mutually pledge to each other our lives, our fortunes and our sacred honor.\n\n- Thomas\n|\nWhen no one you know tells the truth, you learn to see under the surface.\n\n- Cassandra Clare, Lady Midnight\n|\nHis entire body was pleading for reassurance, and if her whole love was not enough what else could she give him to cure his doubt?\n\n- Anaïs Nin, The Four-Chambered Heart: V3 in Nin's Continuous Novel\n|\nThe sky seemed abruptly to have had enough of my dithering and dramatically lightened up around the glowing moon, which retreated like an aging sovereign before the rising sun.\n\n- Mary Ellen Hannibal, Citizen Scientist: Searching for Heroes and Hope in an Age of Extinction\n|\nWe could get kinky and see how bats and rats make love, he suggested in a whisper, warm breath against her neck.You are a sick man, Jacques. Very, very sick.\n\n- Christine Feehan, Dark Desire\n|\nThe advantage of being married a long time was that one could argue without the necessity of the other's actual, physical presence.\n\n- William\n|\nThree ways to Change: First is behaving Positively, Second is behaving Positively and the Third is stop being Negative.'- Gavhi Theron.P\n\n- Gavhi\n|\nYou can't call your life your own: and in return you have safety, if it's worth having at the price you pay.\n\n- Richard Adams, Watership Down\n|\nThe personality susceptible to the dream of limitless freedom is a personality also prone, should the dream ever sour, to misanthropy and rage.\n\n- Jonathan Franzen, Freedom\n|\nWildflowers can't be controlled, and neither can the girl with a soul boundless as the sky, and a spirit as free and wild as the ocean.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nIf we have no peace, it is because we have forgotten that we belong to each other.\n\n- Mother\n|\nFor a peaceful world, the golden rules to live by are mutual understanding, respect, tolerance, forgiveness, and love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI am too sick to be out of bed, too crazy to sleep, and am surrounded by horrors.\n\n- Horace\n|\nSome instances in life call for humility. But, sometimes you need to be flat-out brazen when it comes to the desires of your heart.\n\n- Nakia\n|\nSometimes we need to just brush away our pride, break down the walls around our hearts, and open up to those we truly care for.\n\n- Imania\n|\nIt struck me as particularly suspicious that Yahweh was described as being remarkably human. I mean, seriously; this God is, at times, almost too human.\n\n- Michael Vito Tosto, Portrait of an Infidel: The Acerbic Account of How a Passionate Christian Became an Ardent Atheist\n|\nWhen I first met you, that's what I remember. I looked up at the sky and thought, I'm going to love this person because even the sky looks different.\n\n- Margaret Stohl, Beautiful Chaos\n|\nWhen your dreams get fulfilled in dreams, wouldn’t you rather skip reality?\n\n- Nico\n|\nWe all know that it is women who take the decisions, but we have to let men think that the decisions are theirs. It is an act of kindness on the part of women.\n\n- Alexander McCall Smith, The Full Cupboard of Life\n|\nFor all of my life, I am digging deep in my heart to find the liquid gold of love to share.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nNo one cared what St. Louis thought, although the city got a wink for pluck.\n\n- Erik Larson, The Devil in the White City: Murder, Magic, and Madness at the Fair That Changed America\n|\nWhat did the soup say to the tea plate? 'You're too shallow for me. I like deep dish to dip right into!' I still keep my British humour in good taste. No room for egos or rumours.\n\n- Ana\n|\nPessimists never go on a voyage of discovery, equally so they never leave the shoreline in search of new horizons.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nIn art, questions are always more interesting than answers.\n\n- Marcus Berkmann, Set Phasers to Stun: 50 Years of Star Trek\n|\nIf that's what you want to do, then you should go do it-and do it well.\n\n- John Wood, Creating Room to Read\n|\nOn the occasions that he did look up from the page, he would seem as though he were awakening from a dream.\n\n- Laini Taylor, Strange the Dreamer\n|\nIf you can dream it, you can do it.\n\n- Walt\n|\nTo live is the rarest thing in the world. Most people exist, that is all.\n\n- Oscar\n|\nThe earth grieves, and I grieve, and I am weary of the fight\n\n- Sherryl Jordan, Winter of Fire\n|\nReach out, with all your heart, to your divine-dreams.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nThe idea of living forever makes me uncomfortable, and at this point I've lived long enough and seen enough Twilight Zone episodes to know that there's always a catch.\n\n- Mara Wilson, Where Am I Now?\n|\nFeed your child ideas of peace, harmony and compassion but at the same time give them courage to defend their identity and dignity.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Human Making is Our Mission: A Treatise on Parenting\n|\nPeace and love, peace and love!\n\n- Ringo\n|\nStarting out a new day gives hope for new adventures, villains and hero's to cross your path. Make the most of it.\n\n- Anastasia\n|\nWestern funerals: black hearses, and black horses, and fast-fading flowers. Why should black be the colour of death? Why not the colours of a sunset?\n\n- Daniele Varè, The Maker of Heavenly Trousers\n|\nFrom sunrise to sunset to sunrise, there is a lifetime of beauty, charm and elegance.\n\n- Sandeep\n|\nIn the world we live in, priests and bartenders have a lot in common.\n\n- Flavia Biondi, La generazione\n|\n…on some occasions, women, like dreams, go by contraries.\n\n- Louisa May Alcott, Little Women\n|\nFor the sun, stars, oceans, and all the trees, I’ll consider it.\n\n- Jandy Nelson, 