tracted, rarely fully present. Weird people silence the distractions and remain fully in the moment.\n\n- Craig Groeschel, Weird: Because Normal Isn't Working\n|\nI thought that the light-house looked lovely as hope,That star on life's tremulous ocean.\n\n- Thomas\n|\nI can't tell you how terribly glad I am that you're going to be all right,' George said, rather thickly. 'I...I wouldn't know how to act without a twin.\n\n- Sarah Brazytis, The Apprentices\n|\nIF SOMEONE KEEPS DOING WHAT THEY'RE DOINGTHEY WILL GET BETTER AT IT, BUT.... THEY STILL WON'T BE BETTER THEN YOU!KEEP PUSHING!\n\n- Qwana Reynolds-Frasier, Friend In Your Pocket Conversations Session One\n|\nBut the purpose and nature are never clearly revealed. Human behaviour is a series of lunges, of which, it is sometimes sensed, the direction is inevitable.\n\n- Patrick White, Voss\n|\nTreat everyone with politeness and kindness, not because they are nice, but because you are.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nWhen people stargazing, they stare at stars,and many other things which they've already presumed commonly and universally as stars.\n\n- Toba Beta, Betelgeuse Incident: Insiden Bait Al-Jauza\n|\nIf you hit bottom, there's a whole lot of people here to help you up\n\n- Suzanne Collins, Gregor and the Code of Claw\n|\nGod is my strength and my defense. When I am weak, he makes me strong. When I am broken, he makes me whole.\n\n- Amaka Imani Nkosazana, Sweet Destiny\n|\nThe trick and the beauty of language is that it seems to order the whole universe, misleading us into believing that we live in sight of a rational space, a possible harmony.\n\n- John Burnside, The Dumb House\n|\nThe power of hope! Even a lack of ambition can, for a time, pay off as a necessary facet, as long as hope outweighs it.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nBut what if all the tranquility, all the comfort, all the contentment were now to come to a horrifying end?\n\n- Franz\n|\nWinning is great, but if it's not enough then then you'll never have enough!\n\n- Stephen\n|\nDear Non-American Black, when you make the choice to come to America, you become black. Stop arguing. Stop saying I'm Jamaican or I'm Ghanaian. America doesn't care.\n\n- Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie, Americanah\n|\nIf God hadn't rested on Sunday, He would have had time to finish the world.\n\n- Gabriel\n|\nPretend you are a foolish to the tyrant – because if he realizes you are a genius, he might use you to harm others.\n\n- A\n|\nChange is uncomfortable, but it’s helpful!\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Six Words Inspiration\n|\nA man is not called wise because he talks and talks again; but if he is peaceful, loving and fearless then he is in truth called wise.\n\n- Gautama Buddha, The Dhammapada: The Sayings of the Buddha\n|\nNo one can be managed or led, people are inspired and cared for.\n\n- kamil\n|\nIf something happens that causes you Pain, remind yourself that you can’t get the Rainbow without a little Rain.\n\n- RVM\n|\nThings can turn out differently Apollo. That's the nice thing about being human. We only have one life, but we can choose what kind of story it's going to be.\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Hidden Oracle\n|\nMy dream, is to dream, a dream.\n\n- Santosh\n|\nTime is the coin of your life. It is the only coin you have, and only you can determine how it will be spent. Be careful lest you let other people spend it for you.\n\n- Carl\n|\nThing about being free is, comes a point where you can't turn back, even if you wanted to....Even if you wanted to, they wouldn't take you. You've gone to far.\n\n- Nicholas Hochstedler, War in October\n|\nGood intentions aren't enough, you must take right actions.\n\n- Ifeanyi\n|\nIf you don’t know the direction in which you are going, the deep silence of you heart will let you know.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAt some point, you just gotta forgive the past, your happiness hinges on it.\n\n- Aaron Lauritsen, 100 Days Drive: The Great North American Road Trip\n|\nWhen you cross that chasm 